# Test-Driven Development

## TDD Cycle

Before implementing any feature:

1. Write the test file first (pytest)
2. Confirm the test fails as expected
3. Implement the minimum code to pass the test
4. Refactor only after tests pass

## Test Categories (Target: 15+ total)

### Golden Set Regression Tests (R2-Q3, Option A)
- Maintain 15–20 "golden" ads with human-assigned scores across all 5 dimensions
- Run evaluator against golden set as regression test
- Pass condition: evaluator scores within ±1.0 of human-assigned scores on 80%+ of ads
- These tests run before every evaluation batch

### Inversion Tests (R2-Q3, Option C)
- Take high-scoring ads, systematically degrade ONE dimension at a time
- Verify ONLY the degraded dimension's score drops (≥1.5 points)
- Verify other dimensions remain stable (±0.5)
- Minimum: 10 inversion test cases

### Adversarial Boundary Tests (R2-Q3, Option B)
- Perfect Clarity + zero Brand Voice → Clarity high, Brand Voice low
- Wrong brand voice entirely (fast food chain tone) → Brand Voice near 1
- Pure emotional manipulation with no substance → Emotional Resonance high, others low
- CTA that links to nothing → CTA low
- Minimum: 8 adversarial test cases

### Correlation Analysis (R2-Q3, Option C)
- Compute pairwise Pearson correlation across all 5 dimension scores
- Flag any pair with r > 0.7 — this indicates halo effect
- If flagged: the evaluator is not measuring dimensions independently — fix the evaluation prompt
- Run on every batch of 20+ evaluated ads

### Pipeline Integration Tests
- Checkpoint-resume: start pipeline, kill mid-batch, resume — verify identical output
- Compliance filter: known-bad ads caught by all 3 layers
- Token attribution: verify every API call is tagged with purpose
- Seed reproducibility: same inputs → same seed → same outputs
- Brief expansion: verify no hallucinated product claims (output only contains facts from knowledge base)

### Evaluator Drift Tests (R1-Q1)
- Simulate drift by modifying evaluator prompt slightly
- Verify SPC control charts flag the deviation
- Verify canary injection triggers on breach

## Test File Organization

```
tests/
├── test_evaluation/
│   ├── test_golden_set.py       — Regression tests
│   ├── test_inversion.py        — Dimension independence
│   ├── test_adversarial.py      — Boundary cases
│   └── test_correlation.py      — Halo effect detection
├── test_generation/
│   ├── test_brief_expansion.py  — Grounding, no hallucination
│   ├── test_ad_generator.py     — Output format, brand voice selection
│   └── test_compliance.py       — 3-layer compliance filter
├── test_pipeline/
│   ├── test_checkpoint.py       — Resume from crash
│   ├── test_batch_processor.py  — Batch-sequential execution
│   └── test_token_tracking.py   — Attribution correctness
└── test_data/
    ├── golden_ads.json          — Human-scored reference ads
    ├── adversarial_ads.json     — Edge case ads
    └── degraded_ads.json        — Inversion test cases
```

## Do NOT

- Skip writing tests before implementation
- Delete or modify golden set test data without justification
- Use mocks for the evaluator in inversion/adversarial tests — these must test real LLM behavior
- Treat correlation analysis as optional — if dimensions aren't independent, the entire evaluation framework is decorative
